      "metadata_only_seconds_before": [0.158, 0.157, 0.157],
      "metadata_only_seconds_after": [0.131, 0.13, 0.132],
      "dominant_cost": "W4-01 latency miss is a harness measurement artifact (Python reference scan, ~550x the engine). In the Rust loop itself: per-row full StoredMetadata serde_json decode on unfiltered queries (0.157 s/query at 500k rows), plus un-specialized branch-carrying score loops; both repaired with score bit-parity to the brute-force leg preserved.",
      "outcome": "outcome_1_budgets_met",
      "recommendation": "mmap_stands_lance_contingency_shelved"
    },
    "verify_gate": "bash tools/bench_dense_migration.sh --verify-only",
    "production_note": "--verify-only is a deterministic contract gate. The 2026-07-22 W4-01c recovery pass profiled the release-mode Rust engine at the same >=2 GiB isolated scale: warm global 0.371-0.468 s and warm project 0.212-0.221 s, inside the frozen 8 s / 2 s budgets. The earlier OUTCOME 2 reading came from the harness's pure-Python reference scan, which does not execute the engine. Frozen budgets unchanged; the Lance/memex-search contingency stays shelved."
